  "body": "### Description\r\nThe Teku VC will send the following body to the BN as part of the `/eth/v1/validator/beacon_committee_subscriptions` when it needs to get validator duties:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[{\"validator_index\":275394,\"committee_index\":53,\"committees_at_slot\":\"64\",\"slot\":\"3733432\",\"is_aggregator\":false}]\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to [the official spec for this route](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/#/Validator/prepareBeaconCommitteeSubnet), all of these numerical values need to be strings. However, the `validator_index` and `committee_index` here are integers. This is a small but important deviation from the spec that causes a failure when trying the VC to connect to other clients.\r\n\r\nFor example, this causes a deserialization error when trying to connect a Teku VC to a Nimbus BN:\r\n```\r\n{\"code\":\"400\",\"message\":\"Invalid subscription request object(s)\",\"stacktraces\":[\"Unable to deserialize data\"]}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWrapping the `validator_index` and `committee_index` values in quotes, like this:\r\n```\r\n[{\"validator_index\":\"275394\",\"committee_index\":\"53\",\"committees_at_slot\":\"64\",\"slot\":\"3733432\",\"is_aggregator\":false}]\r\n```\r\n\r\nResults in the correct behavior.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Teku's VC successfully connects to a different client's BN and submits successful attestations\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Teku's VC errors out when connecting to a different client's BN\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** 100%\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n* Software version: v22.8.1\r\n* Java version: ---\r\n* OS Name & Version: Debian 11 x64\r\n* Docker Version: 20.10.17\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: N/A",
